  "texts": [
    "Third, the model may not consider potential biases and ethical issues arising from using AI-based predictions to guide student learning and interventions.",
    "Finally, the model needs to be validated and generalized in other educational settings and domains and with other types of data and tasks.",
    "ConclusionsThis paper investigates the use of dynamic interaction patterns in online learning activities and hierarchical relations in student attribute feature spaces to improve the accuracy of model predictions.",
    "A novel academic performance prediction model called APP-DGNN, which employs dual graph neural networks for problem-solving, is proposed.",
    "Specifically, the proposed model uses an interaction-based graph neural network module to learn local academic performance representations from online interaction activities and an attribute-based graph neural network to learn global aca-demic performance representations from attribute features of all students using dynamic graph convolution operations."
